In this case the reason for the reappearance in E is perhaps that the text there has corrections made by Erasmus (αἳ) in the manuscript (cf. Ep. 826), whereas it seems that only the copy by John Smith (Hand D : al) was available for D. It is noticeable too that some of the changes introduced in D are revised in E 3 cf. the differences between D and E in Ep. 279.

Barland’s text in his Epistolae Selectae (App. 12) follows E except in l. 6, where he has iuuat, perhaps only a misprint.]
